</tr>
<tr>
<td>Trustworthiness</td>
<td>Accuracy, transparency, editorial standards</td>
<td>Unchecked AI makes factual errors</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>The 16-month SE Ranking experiment confirmed this pattern. Purely AI-generated pages on new domains without editorial enhancement lost rankings fast. Pages that combined AI production with human editing, original data, and proper E-E-A-T signals maintained or improved their positions.</p>
<p><strong>The practical takeaway:</strong> Google does not penalize AI content. Google penalizes thin, unhelpful content. AI just makes it easier to produce thin content at scale if you lack a strategy.</p>
<p>Understanding <a href="/blog/eeat-google-quality-guide/">what E-E-A-T means for your content</a> is the foundation of any AI content strategy that lasts.</p>
